<%= provide(:title, "Qaddy") %>


<section class="introduction">
    <h2>Attract new online traffic</h2>
    <br />
    <h2>in a cost-efficient way</h2>
    <br />
    <br />

    <button type="button" class="btn btn-large btn-qaddy" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#signupFormContainer" id="signupFormBtn">
      Sign up now
    </button>

    <div id="signupFormContainer" class="collapse">
        <div class="row-fluid">
                <div class="span4 offset4 well">

                    <p>We're currently in <strong>private beta</strong>. Please leave us your data and we'll notify you the minute we open the doors!</p>

                    <%= simple_form_for SignupBeta.new, url: landing_signup_url, remote: true, validate: true, html: { class: 'signupform form well form-vertical', id: 'signupform', :'data-type' => 'json', novalidate: true } do |f| %>

                        <%= f.input :company, input_html: { class: 'span12' } %>
                        <%= f.input :first_name, input_html: { class: 'span12' } %>
                        <%= f.input :last_name, input_html: { class: 'span12' } %>
                        <%= f.input :email, input_html: { class: 'span12' } %>
                        <%= f.input :url, input_html: { class: 'span12' } %>

                        <div class="alert alert-error fade hidden">
                            <button type="button" class="close">&times;</button>
                            <div class="errors"></div>
                        </div>

                        <%= f.submit "Send", class: "btn btn-primary btn-large", disable_with: 'Please wait...' %>

                    <% end %>
                </div>
        </div>
    </div>


    <div class="line-break"></div>
</section><!-- /.introduction -->

<section class="presentation">
    <div class="container">

        <h4>The simplest way to quickly increase your sales<br />by making your customers refer their friends.</h4>

        <div class="row-fluid">
            <article class="span4 presInfo">
                <%= image_tag("presInfo_icon-1.png", alt: "You Buy It", title: "You Buy It") %>
                <h5>You Buy It</h5>
                <p>Clients buy their favorite <br />stuff at your online store<br />in order to receive a code.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="span4 presInfo">
                <%= image_tag("presInfo_icon-2.png", alt: "You Share It", title: "You Share It") %>
                <h5>You Share It</h5>
                <p>They share the recent purchase<br />with their friends at the<br />social network of their choice</p>
            </article>

            <article class="span4 presInfo">
                <%= image_tag("presInfo_icon-3.png", alt: "You Benefit", title: "You Benefit") %>
                <h5>You Benefit</h5>
                <p>Finally they can receive<br />prizes, discounts, new stuff<br />and much more!</p>
            </article>
        </div>

        <article class="scrollBottom">
            <a href="#contentIntroduction" class="scrollArrow slowscroll" title="">Go to How it works</a>
        </article>

    </div>
</section><!-- /.presentation -->


<!-- start CONTAINER -->
<section id="container">
    <div class="container">

        <article id="contentIntroduction" class="content contentIntro">
            <h2>How Qaddy Works</h2>
            <p>Qaddy solves the largest problem faced by e-retailers today:<br />How to attract new online traffic in a cost-efficient way.</p>
            <div class="lineBr"></div>
            <br class="clear" />
        </article>

        <div class="row-fluid">
            <article class="content">
                <h3><strong>Step 1:</strong> Clients purchase.</h3>

                <div class="span5 offset1">
                    <p>So the process starts like this: You click on the sign up button above, where you will have to fill a few simple fields. After this you will be ready to get the benefits our platform has to offer.</p>
                    <p>Then, your clients will start visiting your store and spend some time on it. They take a look on a few products they might want to buy, to finally decide which of those products better fit their needs and purchase a number of them, which obviously they liked very much.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="span5">
                    <%= image_tag("images_how-to-1.jpg", alt: "Step 1", title: "Step 1", class: "img-polaroid") %>
                </div>

                <div class="lineBr"></div>
                <br class="clear" />
            </article>
        </div>


         <div class="row-fluid">
            <article class="content">
                <h3><strong>Step 2:</strong> They get notified.</h3>

                <div class="span5 offset1">
                    <%= image_tag("images_how-to-2.jpg", alt: "Step 2", title: "Step 2", class: "img-polaroid") %>
                </div>

                <div class="span5">
                    <p>You may think <i>"So what… Step 1 is obvious"</i>. Well, here comes the interesting part where <strong>Qaddy</strong> takes place.</p>
                    <p>Customers who have purchased a product will receive an e-mail, notifying them of the purchase and getting a clickable link that they can use to refer their friends the products they have just acquired.</p>
                    <p>If they finally do, you will be expanding the amount of people that visits your store, making them become potential clients.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="lineBr"></div>
                <br class="clear" />
            </article>
        </div>

        <div class="row-fluid">
            <article class="content">
                <h3><strong>Step 3:</strong> Clients refer their friends!</h3>

                <div class="span5 offset1">
                    <p>When they click the link on the notification e-mail, customers will be redirected to a page which contains the list of products they have purchased.</p>
                    <p>Once in there, they will have to Login with their <strong>Facebook account</strong> in order to be able to refer.</p>
                    <p>Each product on the list will have its proper name and picture. Then below a field where they can write anything they would like to add about the purchased product.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="span5">
                    <%= image_tag("images_how-to-3.jpg", alt: "Step 3", title: "Step 3", class: "img-polaroid") %>
                </div>

                <br class="clear" />
            </article>
        </div>

    </div>

</section>

<!-- Success modal -->
<div id="successModal" class="modal hide fade" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="successModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-header">
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">×</button>
        <h3 id="successModalLabel">Thank You!</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="modal-body">
        <p>Thank you! We'll notify you the minute we open the doors!</p>
    </div>
    <div class="modal-footer">
        <button class="btn" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">Close</button>
    </div>
</div>

